definition[0]: to leave a job or position so that it is available for someone else to do
example[0]: Clay will vacate the position on June 19.
definition[1]: to leave a seat, room etc so that someone else can use it
example[1]: Guests must vacate their rooms by 11:00.
definition[2]: to leave a job, position etc
example[2]: Mr Jones was elected to fill the board seat vacated by Mr Carlisle
definition[3]: to officially cancel a decision made by a court of law
example[3]: The court vacated the compensation award and sent it for new hearings.
